Instead of creating a reference to an existing object you can create the object itself inside ``Ili9341``:

Change

    ILtdc &amp; ltdc;

in ``Ili9341`` to

    Ltdc ltdc;

And remove the temporary object ``Ltdc()`` from the initializer:

    Ili9341:: Ili9341() noexcept : 
        ltdc()
    { }

If you do not want make the element ``ltdc`` *public* inside ``Ili9341`` you can make it *private* and add a public get function like

    ILtdc &amp; getLtdc(void);

returning a reference to ``ltdc``.

